<subSubSection id="A68180CB7DA2B9BD23947689B827D56C" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="DE85EBA8468B1810FAF9774C013738F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3035F204F550AAFF34217CEBC086CF54" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName id="051BC7165B06A1842F5EB89872F2C3D2" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1930" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophioplinthaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophioplinthaca defensor" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="defensor">
<emphasis id="462762DD12466B31F7BCC46AB0C28030" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophioplinthaca defensor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by 
<bibRefCitation id="455BB94F3473DFC0256725D50D94FD37" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorisk Forening" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 295" refId="B23" refString="Koehler, R, 1930. Ophiures recueillies par le Docteur Th. Mortensen dans les Mers d'Australie et dans l'Archipel Malais. Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914-1916. LIV. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorisk Forening 89: 1 - 295" title="Ophiures recueillies par le Docteur Th. Mortensen dans les Mers d'Australie et dans l'Archipel Malais. Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 1916. LIV." volume="89" year="1930">Koehler (1930)</bibRefCitation>
based on a single specimen. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="7F114E392D65F5B020F1276F4E3639B5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13131-020-1666-1" author="Na, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Oceanologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B39" refString="Na, J, Chen, W, Zhang, D, Zhang, R, Lu, B, Shen, C, Zhou, Y, Wang, C, 2021. Morphological description and population structure of an ophiuroid species from cobalt-rich crust seamounts in the Northwest Pacific: Implications for marine protection under deep-sea mining. Acta Oceanologica Sinica 40 (12): 1 - 11, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s13131-020-1666-1" title="Morphological description and population structure of an ophiuroid species from cobalt-rich crust seamounts in the Northwest Pacific: Implications for marine protection under deep-sea mining." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13131-020-1666-1" volume="40" year="2021">Na et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
provided rich details of morphological variation from juvenile to adult 
<taxonomicName id="B388DDAF31FB594648FB5DF2B8B26811" genus="O." lsidName="O. defensor" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="defensor">
<emphasis id="20539F1D97FBDC9D2A4532E678756D3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. defensor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the specimen from our collection concurs with their intraspecific morphological variations (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1CFA94CC6A2EF9FD15F9C4EB5C4BDC59" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Ophioplinthaca semele (A. H Clark, 1949) (IDSSE-EEB-SW 0113: A-H) A dorsal disc B ventral disc C center of the disc D radial shield E oral frame F ventral arm G dorsal arm H lateral arm; Ophioplinthaca defensor Koehler, 1930 (IDSSE-EEB-SW 0112: I-Q) I dorsal disc J ventral disc K center of the disc L disc spine M oral frame N lateral disc O dorsal arm P ventral arm Q lateral arm. Abbreviations: as adoral shield, dap dorsal arm plate, das dorsal arm spine, gs genital slit, j jaw, lap lateral arm plate, m madreporite, os oral shield, rs radial shield, ts tentacle scale, vap ventral arm plate, vas ventral arm spine. Scale bars: 2 mm (I); 1 mm (A, B, F-H, J, N-P); 500 µm (C-E, K, M, Q); 200 µm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1099.76479.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682275" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">14I-Q</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
